message.content: A cup is a cylindrical-shaped vessel with a handle, used for drinking beverages. It is usually made of ceramic, glass, plastic, or metal materials. The size and shape of a cup can vary, but most cups have a wider opening at the top and a narrower base. Cups can come in different colors and patterns, and some may have a textured or glossy surface. Cups can be found in kitchens, dining areas, offices, restaurants, cafes, and other places where beverages are consumed. The visual characteristics of a cup include its material, size, shape, color, pattern, and surface texture.
